CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, pg. 17 reads: "Greet C. of C. Dinner Guest - Dr. E. Jerry Walker, fourth form left, pastor of the integrated St. James Methodist Church ,Chicago, who addressed the Council of Churches' race fellowship dinner at First Baptist Church, Monday evening this week, exchanges greetings with members of the sponsoring committee, left to right: The Rev. C.H. Foggie, interracial committee chairman; the Rev. Donald A. Beard, dinner chairman; Mrs. Daisy Lampkin, promoter; Dr. Walker, the Rev. R.L. Kinchjoe, executive secretary, and the Rev. G.F. Nelson, a member of the committee. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Rev. Charles H. Foggie, Rev. Donald A. Beard, Daisy Lampkin, Dr. E. Jerry Walker, Rev. R. L. Kinchjoe, and Rev. G. F. Nelson, standing in First Baptist Church
